Certainly! Designing a target HUD (Heads-Up Display) can be both functional and visually appealing. Let’s brainstorm some elements you can incorporate into your target HUD: Target Information: Display the name or identifier of the target (e.g., enemy name, vehicle type). Health bar or percentage to indicate the target’s remaining health. Shield or armor status if applicable. Crosshair: A central crosshair to help players aim accurately. Consider customizing the crosshair style (dot, lines, etc.). Distance Indicator: Show the distance between the player and the target. Use icons (e.g., meters, feet) to represent distance units. Ammo Count: If the player’s weapon has limited ammo, display the remaining rounds. Consider using icons (bullets, magazines) for clarity. Objective Markers: Indicate mission objectives or waypoints. Use arrows or icons to guide players toward their goal. Status Effects: Show debuffs or buffs affecting the player or target. Examples: Poisoned, on fire, stunned, etc. Compass or Mini-Map: Display nearby enemies, allies, and points of interest. Highlight the target’s location relative to the player. Reticle Animations: Add subtle animations to the crosshair or reticle. For example, a pulsing effect when the crosshair is over an enemy. Customizable Elements: Allow players to adjust HUD elements (size, opacity, position). Provide options for color customization. Sound Feedback: Trigger audio cues when the crosshair is on target. Different sounds for hitting, missing, or critical hits.

has anyone been able to use worldtoscreen correctly, anything i try gives really weird results, text renders super far off inteded spot etc
winnie 30/06/2024 6:12 pm
heres an old example custom nametags script with worldToScreen int color = new Color(0, 0, 0, 255).getRGB(); void onRenderTick(float partialTicks) { for (Entity en : client.getWorld().getPlayerEntities()) { if (en.isDead() || en.getNetworkPlayer() == null || !client.render.isInView(en)) { continue; } Vec3 position = en.getPosition(); Vec3 lastPosition = en.getLastPosition(); position.x = interpolate(position.x, lastPosition.x, partialTicks); position.y = interpolate(position.y, lastPosition.y, partialTicks); position.z = interpolate(position.z, lastPosition.z, partialTicks); double heightOffset = position.y + (!en.isSneaking() ? en.getHeight() : en.getHeight() - 0.25) + 0.294; Vec3 screen = client.render.worldToScreen(position.x, heightOffset, position.z, client.getDisplaySize()[2], partialTicks); String displayName = en.getDisplayName(); double distSq = en.getPosition().distanceToSq(client.getPlayer().getPosition()); double posX = screen.x - (client.getFontWidth(displayName) / 2); double posY = screen.y - client.getFontHeight(); client.render.text(displayName, (float) posX, (float) posY, 1, color, true); } } double interpolate(double current, double old, float scale) { return old + (current - old) * scale; }
